		 <img alt="" src="jpg/we_will_direct_you.jpg">
		 &nbsp;<img alt="Welcome" longdesc="Welcome to the wonderful world of genealogy" src="jpg/home_heading.png">
		  
		  <p class="auto-style7"><span class="auto-style9"><strong>Just starting your Genealogical Quest?</strong></span> 
		  In this one-day workshop you will be introduced to genealogy organization and research methods on the 
		  internet and in archives. <strong>
			 <a href="pdf/Kickstart_June4_16.pdf">Register today! </a></strong> </p>
			 
			 <p class="auto-style7">Our members have been preserving, researching, 
			  and publishing their own family histories and that of our 
			  province's families since 1974.
			  </p>
			
			<p class="auto-style7">

			We <strong>welcome</strong> new members and visitors and invite you 
			to check out our<strong> </strong> 
			research services<strong> </strong> 
			and<strong> <span class="auto-style8">FREE</span></strong> 
			<a href="research.html">on-line</a> databases and indexes. Also, be 
			sure to come and browse through our in-house <a href="library.html">library</a> 
			<i>Check back often as our resources are continually updated.</i>
		</p>
			 

 <p class="auto-style7">

			  Members are invited to participate in
			<a href="http://www.agsedm.edmonton.ab.ca/specialinterestgroups.html">Special Interest Groups</a> who meet 
			  regularily to share knowledge, resources and to help solve <i>'genealogical road blocks'</i> relating to a specific country.	
		</p>
		<p class="auto-style7">

			Edmonton

			Branch <strong>
			<a href="http://www.agsedm.edmonton.ab.ca/activities.html">General Meetings</a> </strong>are open to members and non-members.  
			Informative and educational programs are presented at each meeting 
			which will be of interest to genealogists, from beginners to advanced.
		</p>
		<p class="auto-style7">
		
			<strong>The Branch</strong> offers many opportunities for 
			<a href="pdf/Volunteer%20ad.pdf"><strong>volunteer</strong></a> participation: creating indexes from genealogical source material, assisting in the library, cemetery recording, fund raising, and/or serving on a committee.
		</p>
		<br>
		<a href="mailto:edmontonbranchags@gmail.com">Email Us</a> &nbsp; &nbsp;<a href="activities.html#meetings">Scheduled Meetings</a> &nbsp; &nbsp;  <a href="library.html#map">How to Find Us</a>

